Let's now calculate the present value of the perpetuity.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &=\dfrac{\$6,400}{0.053}
\\[10
pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$120,754.72}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our calculation, the present value of the perpetuity is $120,754.72.

Let's now calculate the value of the perpetuity in the seventh year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$120,754.72}{\left(1 + 0.053\right)^{7}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$120,754.72}{1.4354848}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$84,121.21}
\end{aligned}$$


**Hence, the value or the present value of the perpetuity on the seventh year is $84,121.21.**
